The paper deals with homotopy type theory, which is a branch of mathematics that has connections to computer science, specifically to the study of programming languages and type systems. The paper discusses the truncation operator, which is a concept that is relevant to both logic and category theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses higher inductive types, which are a tool for constructing new types in homotopy type theory, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with category theory, which is relevant to cs.CT (Computational Topology), and homotopy theory, which is relevant to cs.HO (Homotopy Theory).
